records.addlTxt:
Defendant Eric M Evans in court with Attorney Andrew Joel Golden.  Catelin Ringersma appeared for the State of Wisconsin.

Matter is here for sentencing.  Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the State, defense and defendant.  

AS TO COUNT #1:  The Court sentenced the defendant to serve SIX (6) MONTHS in the House of Correction, STRAIGHT TIME with credit for THREE (3) DAYS time served.

AS TO COUNT #2:  The Court sentenced the defendant to serve NINE (9) MONTHS in the House of Correction, STRAIGHT TIME CONSECUTIVE to count #1.  The Court STAYED this sentence and placed the defendant on probation for a period of ONE YEAR CONSECUTIVE to count #1 with the following probation conditions:

1) No contact with co-actor, Avashon Devon; no contact with Potawatomi Casino; 
2) Any Counseling the Department of Corrections deem appropriate; 
3) Restitution in the amount of $5,100, joint and several with 15CF1697--Avashon Devon, to victim, Potawatomi Casino;
4) Pay supervision fees;
6) Provide a DNA sample - pay surcharge; 
7) Pay all remaining mandatory costs, fees, surcharges and assessments by the end of probation period or balance to convert to civil judgment;

Filed,
Pretrial Incarceration Credit;
Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief.
